<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-01T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-01T10:00:00-04:00">September
                                    1, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>163. Your 279, August 31, 5 p.m. Please inform Aranha that the American
                            Chargé d’Affaires in La Paz has been instructed to continue normal
                            relations with the present Bolivian Government. No question of
                            recognition has been raised by this Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>